  • Classes in hillbillies.model used by hillbillies.common.internal.providers 
    Class and Description
    Unit
    A class of Units which can have a name, agility, strength, weight, toughness, maximum hitpoints, maximum staminapoints, current hitpoints, current staminapoints, orientation, cube coordinates, position, default behaviour, a Faction, a Task and several speeds.
  • Classes in hillbillies.model used by hillbillies.model 
    Class and Description
    Boulder
    A class describing the Boulders that are active in the World.
    Faction
    A class describing Factions that are active in the World, with a set of Units and a Scheduler.
    Log
    A class describing Logs that are active in the World.
    Scheduler
    A class describing the Scheduler, which is attached to a Faction and stores Tasks.
    Task
    A class of Tasks than can be assigned to Units, with a name, priority, activity, list of schedulers, variable declarations and a selected coordinate.
    Unit
    A class of Units which can have a name, agility, strength, weight, toughness, maximum hitpoints, maximum staminapoints, current hitpoints, current staminapoints, orientation, cube coordinates, position, default behaviour, a Faction, a Task and several speeds.
    World
    A class describing the World in which the game is played, containing a TerrainChangeListener, a 3D array which describes the terrain, a ConnectedToBorder object, a set of Units, a set of Factions, a set of Boulders and a set of Logs.
    WorldObject
    A class of objects that are in the World.
